 Asia: Digital Content Identity Construction within the Animation Landscapes of Japan and Thailand}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Otaku Market in Japan: Key Research Findings 2011\">{{cite web | url=http://www.yanoresearch.com/press/pdf/1002.pdf | title=Otaku Market in Japan: Key Research Findings 2011 | publisher=Yano Research | accessdate=12 August 2013 | author=October 26, 2011 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141218055751/http://www.yanoresearch.com/press/pdf/1002.pdf | archive-date=18 December 2014 | url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Otaku Market in Japan: Key Research Findings 2012\">{{cite web | url=http://www.yanoresearch.com/press/press.php/001002 | title=Otaku Market in Japan: Key Research Findings 2012 | publisher=Yano Research Institute | date=October 15, 2012 | accessdate=12 August 2013 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170630031233/http://www.yanoresearch.com/press/press.php/001002 | archive-date=30 June 2017 | url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Otaku Spaces Book\">{{cite web | url=http://www.androniki.com/blog/otaku-spaces-book/ | title=Otaku Spaces Book | publisher=Androniki Christodoulou | accessdate=19 August 2013 | author=Christodoulou, Androniki | url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130901021523/http://www.androniki.com/blog/otaku-spaces-book/ | archivedate=1 September 2013 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Otaku harassed as sex-crime fears mount\">{{cite news|title=Otaku harassed as sex-crime fears mount|url=http://search.japantimes.co.jp/cgi-bin/fd20050206t3.html|newspaper=The Japan Times|accessdate=August 19, 2013|author=Michael Hoffman|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071216162834/http://search.japantimes.co.jp/cgi-bin/fd20050206t3.html|archivedate=December 16, 2007 |date=February 6, 2005}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Otaku uses manga and anime to improve Foreign Affairs\">{{cite web | url=http://paper.wenweipo.com/2008/09/23/GJ0809230014.htm | title=Otaku uses manga and anime to improve Foreign Affairs |