former'', a 1986 [[List of Sega arcade games|Sega arcade game]]\n\n==Science and technology==\n* [[Transformer (gene)]], a family of genes that regulate sex determination in some insects\n* [[Transformer (flying car)]], a DARPA military project\n* [[Asus Transformer]], a series of hybrid tablet computers\n* [[Switched-mode power supply]] or, in extra-low-voltage lighting applications, \"electronic transformer\"\n* [[TrikeBuggy Transformer]], a U.S. powered hang glider\n*[[Transformer (machine learning model)]], a deep learning architecture\n\n==Other uses==\n* [[Transformer (spirit-being)]], an indigenous tradition of the Pacific Northwest of North America\n* [[Prada Transformer]], a building in Seoul, South Korea\n\n==See also==\n* [[Transformers (disambiguation)]]\n\n{{disambiguation}}\n", "name_user": "BAS2017", "label": "safe", "comment": "Reworded the entry for electronic transformers to be consistent with the other entries, i.e. {a reference to some sort of 'transformer'} followed by a description and/or links to appropriate Wikipedia articles.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Transformer_(disambiguation)"}
